-- Mubadala Cancels Tenders for $1.36 Billion Soccer Stadium, MEED Reports
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-13T13:32:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/mubadala-cancels-tenders-for-1-36-billion-soccer-stadium-meed-reports.html
Mubadala Development Co., an
investment unit of Abu Dhabi government, cancelled a tender to
build a 5 billion-dirham ($1.36 billion) soccer stadium in the
emirate, MEED reported, citing letters the company sent to
contractors.  Mubadala confirmed the project was put on hold "until
further notice," according to the report. It said tender bonds
for the project were due to expire on Oct. 17 after the bid
deadline of June 21.  Mubadala received five bids from Sinohydro Corp. and groups
led by Bouygues SA, Samsung Corp., Taisei Corp., and Vinci
Grands Projects, according to the report.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
